All shoddy audio can usually be fixed with good vlc audio settings. Here are mine:

"GRAPHIC EQUALIZER"

PRESET: FLAT
ENABLED
2 PASS: Yes
PREAMP: 10.4DB
60HZ: -14.3DB
170HZ: -9.4DB
310HZ: -1.7DB
600HZ: +0.7DB
1KHZ: -0.47DB
6KHZ: -2.70DB
14KHZ: 7.2DB
16KHZ: -4.2DB

"COMPRESSOR"
ENABLED
RMS/PEAK: 0.2
ATTACK: 42.7MS
RELEASE: 43.3MS
THRESHOLD: -18DB
RATIO: 3.1:1
KNEE RADIUS: 3.2DB
MAKEUP GAIN: 7.1DB

"SPATIALIZER"
ENABLED
SIZE:0.1
WIDTH: 0.5
WET: 0.2
DRY: 0.8
DAMP: 0.3

with these settings the movie is 10x more watchable. I have an ear for these things so I hope I make your experience more enjoyable. If you don't like it, then I apologize, I tried my best.

-ATOMIC
